  <description type="morphology">Corms elongate or becoming rhizomes. Leaves 10–14 cm, 1–4(–5) mm wide. Heads in dense, spiciform arrays (closely spaced, stems usually obscured by heads). Involucres 10–14 mm. Phyllaries in 4(–5) series. Florets 4–8. 2n = 20, 40, 60.</description>
